article.headline: Nevada 77, Vermont 62
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Marcellus Kemp scored 24 points and No. 22 Nevada beat Vermont 77-62 on Wednesday night to snap the Catamounts' 14-game home winning streak. Kemp was 8-of-12 from the field and 7-of-8 from the line for the Wolf Pack (2-0) in their 11th consecutive road victory. Nick Fazekas added 20 points, and Mo Charlo had 13 points and 14 rebounds for Nevada. Martin Klimes led Vermont (0-3) with a career-high 24 points, and freshman Mike Trimboli had 19 points, six assists and four steals in his Patrick Gym debut. "We had two key players sick but we were able to gut out a win," Nevada coach Mark Fox said. "Give credit to Vermont for a great game plan and they really hustled. They made some big shots and Klimes is much more physical and skilled than last season. He never takes a play off. Mo Charlo did a great job on the boards for us and Marcellus gave us a huge lift off the bench." Nevada made its first eight shots from the field and never trailed. "It has been the same story all season long," first-year Vermont coach Mike Lonergan said. "We battled hard but came up short at the end. I am real happy with our effort and how we competed and I can't say enough about our fans."
